      <h3>Seaside view of Aqaba and the Red Sea</h3>
      <p>Famed for its preserved coral reefs and unique sea life, this ancient Red Sea port city is home to the Mameluk Fort, used as a khan (travellers’ inn) for pilgrims on their way to Mecca. The beautiful fort is marked with various inscriptions marking the latter period of the Islamic dynasty. In Aqaba, visit ancient, mud-brick Ayla (Ancient Church), which is the oldest, purpose-built church in the world. Aqaba also hosts the house of Sharif Hussein Bin Ali, the great grandfather of King Abdullah II.</p>
